    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A technique used to visually determine the shrinkage temperature (Ts) of skin and leather, as an indicator of the collagen’s hydrothermal stability. A prepared sample is covered with distilled water, placed on a Kofler hotbench, then heated at the appropriate heating rate.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
